node.text: The return of Barry the Base Ten Man!!! Understanding base ten relationships and the power of ten as an 8 year old is kind of like understanding how to do your own taxes as a thirty-something year old. So enter Barry! First we describe and identify the names of the blocks (units, rods, flats, and cubes), discuss the digits and values that make up his face, and then explore ways to rename those numbers based on groups of ten. For example, the value of Barry’s nose is 1,000, which is the same as 10 hundreds or 100 rods. It mostly blows their minds 🤪, but we’re making progress! You can find Barry here 👉🏼 https://bit.ly/BarryTheBaseTenMan Magnetic base ten blocks from @lakeshorelearning #barrythebasetenman #iteachthird #thirdistheword #placevalue #basetenblocks #teachersofinstagram #teachersfollowteachers #mybrainhurts

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Amy Groesbeck on August 26, 2021.

node.text: Establishing voice levels up in here! We talked about each voice level, the mini humans provided examples of where and when each level is appropriate, and then we practiced what they sounds like. Quick, easy, and purposeful!  Shoutout to @pearceinprimary for the sticky note sorting idea! #voicelevels #thirdistheword #handsonlearning #iteachthird #teachersfollowteachers #teachersofinstagram #itsloudupinhere

node.text:
DIY DRY ERASE CLIPBOARD TUTORIAL!
1️⃣ Cut dry erase contact paper the length of a clipboard
2️⃣ Peel away backside of the contact paper 
3️⃣ Place sticky side of contact paper on the backside of the clipboard and smooth out any air bubbles
4️⃣ Trim excess paper using a utility knife
5️⃣ Paint and decorate the front side of the clipboard
I found all of the supplies at @HEB AND there’s a coupon for that! They’re offering Texas educators 15% off, so you can use your school email to sign up at heb.com/teachers or tap the link in my profile to snag your coupon!
#diyclassroom #hebteacher #sponsored
